This paper proposes a scientific reasoning system that uses objective evidence in the form of independent experimental trials, propositional axioms, and constraints on the probabilities of events. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories, as it deals with developing a reasoning system. Additionally, the paper discusses managing uncertainty in a rule-based expert system, which could fall under the sub-categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions the potential application of the system in medicine, which could also place it in the sub-category of Databases (cs.DB).
